{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06561db14105d8e5942ab87719ad60e3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## Trust States\n\n| Trust State | Meaning | When it occurs |\n|---|---|---|\n| `static_verified` | All facts passed static verification only | `verification_mode = \"static\"` with 0 rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:131`) |\n| `partial_static` | Some facts rejected by static verifier | `verification_mode = \"static\"` with ≥1 rejected fact (`src/cluster.ts:131`) |\n| `llm_verified` | All static-passed facts also passed LLM verification and were promoted | `verification_mode = \"llm\"` with 0 total rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:221`) |\n| `partial_llm` | Some facts rejected by LLM verifier; promoted facts upgraded to `llm_verified` confidence | `verification_mode = \"llm\"` with ≥1 total rejected fact (`src/cluster.ts:221`) |\n| `unprepared` | No factsheet ever created | Cluster created, never prepared |\n| `untrusted` | Factsheet marked stale or needs re-prepare | `markClusterFactsheetStale` / `markClusterNeedsPrepare` (`src/db.ts:867,877`) |\n\n## The distinguishing field: `omitted_facts`\n\n`src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-182` shows the differentiation:\n\n```ts\nconst omittedFacts = typeof content.omitted_facts === \"number\" ? content.omitted_facts : 0;\nif (status === \"llm_verified\") {\n  return omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_llm\" : \"llm_verified\";\n}\nreturn omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_static\" : \"static_verified\";\n```\n\n`omitted_facts` accumulates rejected counts from both static verifier and LLM verifier (`src/cluster.ts:220`).\n\n## Consult gating\n\n`cluster_consult` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:55`) only trusts a factsheet if:\n- `factsheet.status === \"llm_verified\"`, **or**\n- `cluster.static_factsheet_policy === \"allow\"` (allows `static_verified` too)\n\nSo `partial_static` and `partial_llm` are effectively consult-blocked without operator override — they exist as audit artifacts but cannot serve `cluster_consult` calls."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":129783,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1bc568d1-5a5f-4314-b4be-00aca006f5e1","uuid":"7923956f-e8a9-4b1a-9b61-9d9105c96568"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":39312,"duration_api_ms":39267,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\n## Trust States\n\n| Trust State | Meaning | When it occurs |\n|---|---|---|\n| `static_verified` | All facts passed static verification only | `verification_mode = \"static\"` with 0 rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:131`) |\n| `partial_static` | Some facts rejected by static verifier | `verification_mode = \"static\"` with ≥1 rejected fact (`src/cluster.ts:131`) |\n| `llm_verified` | All static-passed facts also passed LLM verification and were promoted | `verification_mode = \"llm\"` with 0 total rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:221`) |\n| `partial_llm` | Some facts rejected by LLM verifier; promoted facts upgraded to `llm_verified` confidence | `verification_mode = \"llm\"` with ≥1 total rejected fact (`src/cluster.ts:221`) |\n| `unprepared` | No factsheet ever created | Cluster created, never prepared |\n| `untrusted` | Factsheet marked stale or needs re-prepare | `markClusterFactsheetStale` / `markClusterNeedsPrepare` (`src/db.ts:867,877`) |\n\n## The distinguishing field: `omitted_facts`\n\n`src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-182` shows the differentiation:\n\n```ts\nconst omittedFacts = typeof content.omitted_facts === \"number\" ? content.omitted_facts : 0;\nif (status === \"llm_verified\") {\n  return omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_llm\" : \"llm_verified\";\n}\nreturn omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_static\" : \"static_verified\";\n```\n\n`omitted_facts` accumulates rejected counts from both static verifier and LLM verifier (`src/cluster.ts:220`).\n\n## Consult gating\n\n`cluster_consult` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:55`) only trusts a factsheet if:\n- `factsheet.status === \"llm_verified\"`, **or**\n- `cluster.static_factsheet_policy === \"allow\"` (allows `static_verified` too)\n\nSo `partial_static` and `partial_llm` are effectively consult-blocked without operator override — they exist as audit artifacts but cannot serve `cluster_consult` calls.","st